        public org.springframework.context.MessageSource stormpathSpringMessageSource()

      • isPlaceholder

        protected boolean isPlaceholder(org.springframework.context.MessageSource messageSource)
        At ApplicationContext startup, Spring creates a placeholder in the ApplicationContext to await a 'real' message source. This method returns true if the specified message source is just a placeholder (and not relevant for our needs) or false if the message source is a 'real' message source and usable.
        Parameters:
        messageSource - the message source to check
        Returns:
        true if the specified message source is just a placeholder (and not relevant for our needs) or false if the message source is a 'real' message source and usable.
